INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('6', 'how to study java by ourself  ', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">About how to self-learn Java, I think it&#39;s just tapping the code, tapping the code, tapping the code.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;First you have to learn the basics of Java, which is the basics of javase. There are many online tutorials, documents and videos, and you can read and learn on your own. What is more important is Java basic grammar, basic tool classes, collection classes. Multithreading, network programming, and Java reflexes all need to be mastered.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;After learning the basics of Java, we have to learn the Java web, which is very important for JSP, Servlet, javabean and so on. In learning these things, we need to focus on the communication principles of http protocol. This understanding is a good aid to our understanding of Java web, so keep in mind.</span></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">After learning Java web, we will be exposed to framework learning. Now the mainstream framework is SSM(spring + springmvc + mybatis), where spring is the management container, springmvc is the control layer, mybatis is the database connection layer, and these things can be developed after learning.</span></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>', '1559531271375', 'ab56c76ecf574e9ab2b8d9b636ccbdb1.png', '     About how to self-learn Java, I think it\'s just tapping the code, tapping the code, tapping the code.     First you have to learn the basics of J...', '9');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('7', 'Programming life ', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">Faced with programming, please do not be impetuous people</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;, 微软雅黑; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">1. Don&#39;t read the first sentence of someone else&#39;s reply and say: Give me a code! You should think about why. When you think about it and refer to other people&#39;s tips, you know the difference between yourself and others.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">2. Early scholars please do not read too many books that will be mistaken for children. First, look for this system. Many people have been familiar with only some of the functions for a long time. No system is still not enough.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">3. Look for help, do not be a beginner because it is difficult not to look; Help is always the best reference manual, although the help text is sometimes difficult to understand, always feel not intuitive.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">4. Do not be confused by words such as objects, attributes, and methods; The most fundamental thing is to understand the most basic knowledge first.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">5. Don&#39;t miss out on any seemingly simple little problem -- they are often not that simple, or can lead to a lot of knowledge; If you don&#39;t, you &#39;ll never learn.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">6. Knowing something doesn&#39;t mean you can write a script. The script needs experience.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">7. It is not difficult to learn scripts. JSP, ASP, PHP, etc. are not too difficult. What is difficult is to adhere to practice and spare no effort to read books.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">8. Read more books than you can learn. Practice more</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">9. Put the fashionable technology on the mouth, it is better to keep the outdated technology in mind;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">10. One of the best ways to learn scripts is to practice more;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">11. Don&#39;t consider the books in your hands sufficient at any time;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">12. Read the books you can read carefully; If you can&#39;t read a book, try to read it.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">13. Don&#39;t expect to remember and master something with the first reading -- see the second and third;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">14. Please put the examples in the book into practice on the computer, even if there are active documents on the supporting CD;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">15. Expand the meaningful examples seen in the book; And put it into practical use in their own work;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">16. Don&#39;t leave out any of the exercises in the book-please finish them all and record your thoughts;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">17. Don&#39;t stop right away when you find yourself using a poor method in the middle of a script; Please complete the remaining parts of the code as soon as possible to ensure the integrity of the code, then analyze your own errors and rewrite and work.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">18. Don&#39;t worry, it&#39;s not easy to write a script; The level is in the continuous practice consummates and the development;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">19. Every time you learn a script difficulty, try to explain the knowledge to someone and make him understand it -- you can explain it to someone who really understands it;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">20. Record points of knowledge that you have overlooked or did not understand when communicating with others;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">21. Save all the source files you have done-that&#39;s one of your best accumulations;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">22. For the Internet, we still hope that you can make more use of it. Many questions do not have to be asked in forums. First, you must learn to find answers for yourself. For example, Google and Baidu are good search engines. You can find a lot of relevant information by entering keywords. Don&#39;t always wait for others to give you hope, you must be lazy!</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">23, to a forum, you will learn to read previous posts, do not post without looking at anything, perhaps your questions have already been asked, you ask, others do not want to repeat, as a beginner. No one wants their posts to go unanswered.</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">Although it is not a blow to beginners, it is still a place for discussion. If you always expect a master to give you free advice, unless he is your relative! Hey! The discussant, at least at the same level, has a discussion. If the level is really too far away, even the basic operation needs to be answered by others, who will discuss with you?</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">Can find a lot of relevant information, do not always wait for others to give you hope, see that you must be lazy!</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">People who are impetuous are easy to ask: What should I learn? -Don&#39;t ask, just learn;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">The impetuous person is easy to ask: JS money way; -- I suggest you rob a bank;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">The impetuous person is easy to say: I want the Chinese version! I can&#39;t speak English! -No? Learn!</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">There are two kinds of impetuous people: people who only watch and do not learn; One who learns but does not persist;</span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 17px; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">An impetuous person is never a master.</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;, 微软雅黑; font-size: medium; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span></span></p><p><br/></p>', '1559531410120', '290f6afb43db4fedaee4fa315544248f.jpg', '                Faced with programming, please do not be impetuous people1. Don\'t read the first sentence of someone else\'s reply and say: Give me a c...', '6');
